name: BLUBERINI OCTOPUSINI
rhyme: This tiny and chubby marine little chap lives down on the seabed... blup blup blap!

name: TIRILICALICA TIRILICALACO
rhyme: In desert heat, the chicken cried, his feathered chest all glorified. He searched for love through sands so wide - Please let her be a bit frostified!

name: COCCADRILLO FORMAGGIOSO
rhyme: A snoozy croc let out a yawn, quite pleased beneath the morning down. It takes bold dreams, and cheesy pride, to be a slice that's aged inside!

name: PANBRONCIO AL LATTE
rhyme: I'm drenched in milk, a crumbled mess, a snack with deep emotional stress. Don't try to hug this tear-soaked bun - I'm moody food that spoils the fun!

name: MARCO POLLO
rhyme: A rooster brave with travel flair, he spices lands from here to there! He sails at dawn, returns to dine - not one crumb left at lunchtime!

name: OCA DEL ROVER LUNARE
rhyme: With helmet snug on lunar brow, the goose declared, I want it now! Not just to soar like I once planned – my deepest wish to truly land.

name: CACTO IPPOPOTAMO
rhyme: An elegant hippo-cactus, towering and rare, saunters the sands with flamboyant flair.

name: RAPARRAPA CHE PARA
rhyme: Raparrapa dives, loses grip, takes a ride - juggles the ball till the match is tied!

name: CERVELLO PUDDING
rhyme: Cervello Pudding thinks and leans it trembles laughs then quits the scenes It hides in the fridge completely still but melts away when thoughts overfill.

name: GNAMMO SLAMMO E SGOMMO
rhyme: Gnammo Slammo Sgommo speeds in a blaze, yells, chomps, and bounds in echoing craze!

name: AEROMUCCA ARMATA
rhyme: A fighter jet zipped through the blue - surprise! A cow was in the crew. She launched her missiles, wild and proud, mooed with joy and laughed out loud.

name: CAPRAMANTE SOTTOPANCA
rhyme: Caprampante under the bench leaps and lunges starts to clench With springy hooves it bounces through breaks the beat then sticks like glue.

name: CROCODILO POTATINO
rhyme: The crocodile adored the spud, She's wise and round a golden bud She blinked and said a bit confused You're such a gent... with a tubby tater-tude!

name: BONECA AMBALABU
rhyme: La rana che amava la nota contro fuso dentro una ruota Mi sento un'artista che grande emozione Poi rotolò in direzione stazione

name: RUGGINATO LUPOGT
rhyme: That growling wolf, a glam-tuned brute, leased a supercar sleek and cute. He howled through town with turbo flair, then launched the car into the air!

name: BALLERINO LOLOLO
rhyme: I live for dance not belly flab! I'm built to groove - no time to gab!

name: LA VACCA ATOMO ATOMITA
rhyme: I skip the grass, I ditch the well, I glow in space like a stellar spell. Through stars I zip in molten flow - and BOOM like a cosmic volcano!

name: TRIKITRAKATELAS
rhyme: A proud-nosed rhino found his crush a cactus green serene and plush One kiss - kablam! - and by design he joined that prickly valentine

name: APPOLLINO CAPPUCCINO
rhyme: ulla con fare divino ardito sotto un balzo capriccioso Ma d'Baccanale un giro un po' strano gli scivola solo un... e un caso strano!

name: BALLERINA NICOTINA
rhyme: A lovely dancer, lithe and keen, trained on smokes behind the scene. They fuel my plie, they set me free! Then coughed and fell - right in the WC

name: PARARELL BARARELL
rhyme: A giant face Soprano - style beached itself laughing on a chair while Its modern! it shrieked Avant-garde trauma! But the chair just whimpered Call my mama!

name: LUMINARIA FIORENZA
rhyme: A velvet fawn with stealthy grace, the prettiest in her woodland place.

name: RATATINO ROTTAMINO
rhyme: He zipped around, the sewer king, told all the kids, I own this thing! But royalty meant pipes and wet... his trone? A drain. His crown? A bidet set.

name: CHIMPANZINI BANANINI
rhyme: A fuzzy green chimp with fur so bright, lived in a banana, snug and tight.

name: TRALALITA TRALALELITA
rhyme: In heels of red, with flair so fine, a shark paraded down the brine. Fashion is my true vacation! Then tripped... on a seaweed decoration.

name: MANGGA TERKUAT
rhyme: A mango pumped at the local gym, Look! he roared, I'm strong and trim! His fruity muscles looked so stout... till one bad push-out squashed him out.

name: PASTARUGO CALAMARELLO
rhyme: A firm little pasta with moves offbeat danced with a squid on wobbly feet. He tried a tango, but lacked all grace... and splashed in sauce with bold embrace.

name: EVIL BABY OCTI TRIPLETS
rhyme: Three tiny octos in villain disguise, stole strands of seaweed with bashful eyes. We're terror! they cried, We'll bring you pain! then fled in fear to the deep sea domain.

name: SGOMMABIRILLO BRILLO
rhyme: Sgommabiriilo Brillo no longer leads the way, he crashes through signs in wild disarray. He toasts at lights, then hits the brake... this reckless cone made one big mistake.

name: TRIC TRAC BARABOOM
rhyme: The sassy squash without a shoe said, Watch out world - I'm veggie new!

name: LIRILI LARILA
rhyme: An elegant elephant smooth in his stride married a cactus mistaking his bride What passion! What a sweet caress! He cried - then limped away in distress.

name: PLATYPUS BOOS BOOS BOOS
rhyme: The platypus, with puzzled stride, climbed on a bus - quite misaligned. How odd, he said, it won't reach town. And ended up in the savanna, handing sweets around!

name: GARAM MARARAM RARAMAN MARARAMAN DAN MADU DUNGDUNGDUNG TAKTUNGTUNG PERKUNTUNG
description: Nothing makes shelf sense any more
rhyme: A saltshaker proud and made of steel challenged a jar to a dancing deal She tripped on step one with a terrible sound You've cooked a risotto! the jar laughed aloud.

name: TIKTARUGO RITARDONE
rhyme: Tiktarugo crawling past the date skips spring and autumn he's always late He hums the time with no sensation then melts into a mild vibration.

name: APELLONE DI POLLOPELLE
description: The chosen one... with crispy skin
rhyme: Apellone di Pollopelle, winged and fried, soared through flames with crispy pride. He threw his bone like Zeus in rage, and roasted knights right off the stage!

name: DISSASTRULLO CANNIBALO
rhyme: Dissastrulo Cannibalo, wild and spry, does pirouettes with a blade held high. He carves with joy, no evil near: It's melon, friends - not something to fear!

name: MOUSARINI PISTOLINI
description: Quick with words, slow with footing
rhyme: Mousarini, chatty and twitchy too, longed for a shootout with pistols two.

name: TACCHITACCHI ATTACCATICCIO
rhyme: Apellone di Pollopelle, winged and fried, soared through flames with crispy pride. He threw his bone like Zeus in rage, and roasted knights right off the stage!

name: BUDINACCIO DEL DISGUSTO
rhyme: A tuna pudding, baked just right, for a grandpa-cat, a fancy bite. He licked his lips, his eyes went wide - It's art, I guess... with stink inside.

name: CAGNOILNO INSAPONATO
rhyme: Cagnoilno fresh and squeaky clean ran so fast a slippery sheen! He zoomed like a soap-fuelled jet in flight into the laundry - Hey is this alright?

name: PING PONG PONGARO
rhyme: Playing ping-pong with just one toe, a rat looks up and wants to know: What's this madness? What's your song? I say: Pizza? She says: All night long

name: GIRAFFA CELESTE
rhyme: In a sky-blue suit she played her game hide and seek was her claim to fame They can't see me she gave a roar till her neck popped out from a fruity decor.

name: SKIBIDETTO TOALETTO
rhyme: Skibidi Dop Dop Dop Yes Yes Yes!

name: BATATOSO PELOSO, STRAMBO E GULOSO
description: Spud to melt the winter cold
rhyme: He strolled with joy and cuddled tight, his darling spud, his love so right. To the altar! he cried with flair - but mash was all that made it there.

name: PICCIONE MACCHINA
rhyme: With trainers and engine, the pigeon came down, zoomed into Spain like he owned the town. Next stop - Mars! he shouted with glee... then boom went the alien, explosively free!

name: MELANINI PANDANINI
description: An apple a day keeps the panda away
rhyme: An apple once dreamed of a graceful dance, but tripped on a panda in holiday trance. I'm so sorry! she said, quite red - he yawned: It's fine... I'm back to bed.

name: LOS LIRALITOS DICEN LARILA
rhyme: They twirled in sandals, sweet and small, with cactus bellies - ouch for all! Their butts got poked, the crowd went mute... no concert today, just one sore glute!

name: PHONE SELFONE
rhyme: I click my phone with photonic pride, my hamster's selfie goes worldwide. The marmot waves a trombone high, while my ice cream sings a lullaby.

name: STRAND BIER
rhyme: A punk cow drank her fizzy brew, crooned Moooo like stars in a moo-moo revue. On the throne with thunderous might... she earned Milk Obliteration that night!

name: FOMO SAPIENS
rhyme: The Fomo Sapiens stares askew, streams his thoughts in cosmic goo. A digital sage in meme parade, slings hot noodles in a starry charade.

name: BALLERINA CAPPUCCINA
rhyme: Cappuccina twirled with creamy delight, Spinning and sliding from morning to night. She split with a shout: Oh what a routine! and dropped in a mug - extra caffeine!

name: TRALALITO BOCCIOSO
rhyme: Tralalito, fierce and splashy grand, swung his stick with a flipper hand. Let's duel, sea fools! he gave a shout - then tripped on a rock and wiped night out!

name: BITBURGER COIN
rhyme: Come closer, chomp if you dare... but tick me off and I'll scorch the air!

name: RACCRAPAPICCICANTE
rhyme: The creepy frog in a spacey disguise slurped veggie sauce with marshmallow pies. She yelled to the crowd: Antennas? I'm pro! Then bounced away with surfer show.

name: GRATTACIELO LETTERALE
rhyme: A tower of words with rhyming core, lifts me to the alphabet floor. I dine on letter with butter divine, then adjectives serve the final line.

name: GRAIPUSSI MEDUSSI
rhyme: Grape-bodied, zappy, sweet and loose, she danced to jazz with grapey juice. But zipped too far and twirled askew... right into soup - like fruity goo!

name: NUCLEARO DINOSAURO
rhyme: A dino flew with nukes in tow, across the sea in search of foe. Mission complete! he gave a cheer - and hit the highway's busiest tier.

name: RUPIPIPIPI STREAMIMIMIMIMI
rhyme: She posed on cash with selfie charm, and hoped to buy a bigger farm. No likes, no hearts, no viral stream... just grandma's like... and fading dream.

name: ZAMPATIGNA ZOPPICANTE
rhyme: He plays with pebbles no king or ace stitched-up rags all over the place Talks to chickens in country flair and weds a squash with diva air.

name: BABBOBOMBO CARAMELLO
rhyme: He rode a muffler not a sleigh and dripped in fudge by Christmas Day I'm bean Sugar Yum he cried then sizzled off and caramel-fried.

name: FRR FRR CHIMPANIFRITI
rhyme: The jungle hushed, the leaves went still... then out he came with stealth and thrill: Frr Frr Chimpanifriti!

name: KOTLETINO MERKATINO
rhyme: In Frytown's market rage did rise his golden coat was full of lies! This crispy mess? A fried illusion! Thus began the breading revolution!

name: SCIO SCIO CHAMPIGNON
rhyme: Sciò Sciò said Champignon, mad as a hatter, in Klingon shrieks and sporeful chatter. He camouflaged like a lizard in dirt, and screamed from his cap till his roots got hurt!

name: BELERICK
rhyme: Half beak, half bite, in midair he spun - a Gabbeast born from sea and sun!

name: BOMBOCLAT CROCLAT
rhyme: A mutant croc flew through the void, chomping clouds like asteroids. Strike! he roared with scaly zeal, firinga missile surreal!

name: BOMBARISTO SEALSTO SEAL
rhyme: A monk seal strapped with sky appeal, prepped for lift-off, sleek and surreal!

name: BEARORITO APPLEPITOLIROTITO
rhyme: Beaerorito walks, the apple moon's bright, through Big Apple alleys, soft as light.

name: FRIGO CAMELO
rhyme: Into the fridge went the camel, quite mellow, but all he could find was broccoli yellow. No cool breeze? No frozen jell-o? He turned into a charming old fellow!

name: PECORINI LANUSINI
rhyme: The sheep with fringe and wool so light, strummed her noodles with all her might.
